§ 1. In Dig. 8. 1. 3 Paulus defines urban servitudes as those quae in superficie, as contrasted with those quae in solu, consistunt. They are either positive, e. g. tigni immittendi, oneris ferendi, stillicidii avertendi, proiiciendi (right os building some structure such as a balcony out over one's neighbour's land) and cloacae—or negative, secui-ing an advantage to the praedium dominans of which it could be deprived by some altera· tion in the praedium servienS, e. g. altius non tollendi, the right of pre· venting one’s neighbour from raising the height os his house, and ne luminibus or prospectui officiatur.
